==Special inductees==
[[Billy Graham (evangelist)|Billy Graham]] was inducted to the Gospel Music Hall of Fame in 1999 for providing a platform to many Christian artists through the Billy Graham events. These artists include: Michael W. Smith, Amy Grant, Sandi Patty, Larnelle Harris, [[Steven Curtis Chapman]], [[dc Talk]], [[Jars of Clay]]. Others associated with Graham's ministries are also inductees: [[George Beverly Shea]] (soloist of the Billy Graham Evangelistic Team); [[Cliff Barrows]] (music director and choirmaster for all Billy Graham Evangelistic Campaigns); [[Ralph Carmichael]] (producer for the music in Billy Graham films such as "Mr. Texas", "For Pete's Sake", "The Restless Ones", and "His Lane"); and singers [[Ethel Waters]] and [[Stuart Hamblen]].
