'''Sambalpuri drama''' are a typical [[drama]] performance in Sambalpuri Odia language of [[western Orissa]] , [[India]].
==Origin==
The "''naach gaana''" in the streets of villages of the [[western Orissa]] regions are traditionally based on the plots of [[Ramayana]], [[Mahabharata]] and other religion epics.{{cn|date=November 2016}} During the early days Ram-Parshuram bhet was recognized as a form of street play. Currently{{when|date=November 2016}} "[[Ramlila]]" is performed in several villages. Majority of the dramas are performed in open air auditoriums where people stand surrounding the stage to observe. The great visionary Pundit Prayag Dutt Joshi wrote one drama ''Kapat Biha'' in 1936 and it was staged in Raj Khariar in that year.{{cn|date=November 2016}}
==Theatre and Organizations==
*''Sambalpuri drama'' are organized at different parts of [[Western Orissa]] to revive the Sambalpuri drama theater tradition.<ref>[http://www.dailypioneer.com/149202/Week-long-Kosli-drama-fest-in-Balangir-from-Jan-14.html Week-long Kosli drama fest in Balangir from Jan 14]</ref> Generally, artists from different parts of [[Western Orissa]] and other parts of the country are invited for this festival. *''Sambalpuri Naatbadi'' a state level drama festival is also organized at Sadeipali, [[Balangir]] during the month of January.<ref>[http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-01-14/bhubaneswar/28351861_1_theatre-artistes-balangir Kosli theatre fever grips Balangir]</ref> Various cultural organization of Western odisha region participates in the week-long Sambalpuri drama festival. *''Matkhai Mahotsav'', a multilingual theatre festival is also organized in [[Balangir]] town.<ref>[http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-01-27/bhubaneswar/28379458_1_theatre-group-government-matkhai-mahotsav Feminism, sarkari style]</ref> This festival brings artists and cultural troupes from all part of India together. Various local cultural troupes also perform folk musics viz. ''Ghubukudu'' and ''Kendra''. *''Yuba Udayan Association, Jharuapara, Sambalpur'' started in 1997 to bring all the theatre activists together. *''Veer Surendra Sai All Orissa Sambalpuri Drama Competition'' was born for the revival of Sambalpuri drama activities by Yuba Udayan Assosiation, Jharuapara, Sambalpur . In the inaugural year only 19 plays were presented and the next fourteen years witnessed 455 plays being staged. Sambalpuri theatre has engaged scripts, directors and artists to work for performing these dramas. *'' Belpahar Uchhab "Machan"'' 18 to 22 Dec every year *'' Belpahar Uchhab Machan National Theatre festival.'' The festival started in 2004. *''Kranti'' Balangir. A 40 year old drama organization started by Abdul Jamal khan. Kranti Balangir staged around 100 of plays all over India. "Bigul" awarded as best jury award in HINDALCO, Hirakud in all India drama competition. March 30 - March 31 Kranti staged three in kalamandap, [[Balangir]]. One of the most popular play by Kranti is Bigul (the beginning) by Akram Durrani. Swayam Brahma Got 6 awards in Rourkela organised by sangeet natya academy. Akram durrani a young director from [[Western Orissa]].
